    <div class="documentTop">        
        
        <h1>The Department of Sport</h1>
        
        <div class="pageDescription"><p>The department’s areas of responsibility include the administration of the allocation to sport purposes of the surplus from the state-owned gaming company Norsk Tipping, as well as sports centers, sport policy, international sport management, and anti-doping. </p>
<p>The main provision for the allocation of the surplus for sports purposes is that the funds first and foremost should go to development of sports centers/ buildings for sports purposes.</p>
<p>Additionally, funding is provided for the administration and management of the Norwegian Olympic and Paralympic Committee and Confederation of Sports (NIF) as well as for tasks and purposes in sport that the Ministry considers eligible for subsidies. </p>
<p>A number of administrative tasks related to the gaming funds for buildings for sports and physical activities purposes are delegated to municipalities and counties. </p>
</div>        
